  "url": "https://docs.rigetti.com/integration",
  "markdown": "[Skip to main content](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n[![Rigetti](https://docs.rigetti.com/img/rigetti.png)](https://docs.rigetti.com/)[QCS](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/)[Integration](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/)\n[QCS Console](https://qcs.rigetti.com)\n`ctrl``K`\n  * [Integration Documentation](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/)\n  * [Language and Client Tooling](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/language-and-client-tooling)\n  * [Network Access & Infrastructure](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/network-access-and-infrastructure)\n\n\n  * [](https://docs.rigetti.com/)\n  * Integration Documentation\n\n\nOn this page\n# Integration Documentation\nThis space exists to help partners and vendors integrate with Rigetti Quantum Cloud Services (QCS) not specifically for their own use but to offer access to others.\nFor documentation on using QCS to run quantum programs, refer to the [QCS Documentation](https://docs.rigetti.com/).\n## Overview[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#overview \"Direct link to Overview\")\nOur mutual goal in any collaboration is a positive, performant user experience for your platform's end users on Rigetti QCS.\nThere are three key parts in integration:\n  1. Business Agreement: The contracts and communication which define our collaboration. This is out of scope for this technically-focused integration guide, even as they shape each integration.\n  2. Network Access & Infrastructure: Connecting your systems to ours in a secure, performant, and reliable way.\n  3. User Environment: Deciding how and when your users build programs for execution on QCS, and how they submit them. This includes authenticating and authorizing your systems and users for access to QCS.\n\n\n## Terminology[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#terminology \"Direct link to Terminology\")\nThroughout this guide, the terms You or The Partner refers to the organization integrating with Rigetti QCS. Your Platform refers to the suite of software offered by that organization to its users.\n## Common Models[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#common-models \"Direct link to Common Models\")\nWhile each integration is unique, the following models can serve as illustrative templates.\n### Vendor Model[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#vendor-model \"Direct link to Vendor Model\")\n![Vendor Model](https://docs.rigetti.com/assets/images/vendor-model-2f0c50cbf48c45bc315fa9a461b2f24a.png)\n  * In this model, the Partner maintains its own user account management and API for system access.\n  * Users interact only with the Vendor's system directly; the vendor then collects and forwards programs from their systems to QCS, and likewise collects and returns results to their users.\n  * Users may build and submit programs in a format native to QCS (such as Quil), or in a format specified by the Vendor and converted by the Vendor for use on QCS (such as QASM).\n\n\n### Direct User Access Model[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#direct-user-access-model \"Direct link to Direct User Access Model\")\n![Direct User Access Model](https://docs.rigetti.com/assets/images/direct-user-access-model-022836b3854944b9c6462f298585492a.png)\n  * In this partnership, the Partner vets users and forwards requests for accounts with direct access to QCS.\n  * These users then maintain QCS accounts of their own, to include account balances.\n\n\nContinue to [Network Access & Infrastructure](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/network-access-and-infrastructure).\n[Next Language and Client Tooling](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/language-and-client-tooling)\n  * [Overview](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#overview)\n  * [Terminology](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#terminology)\n  * [Common Models](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#common-models)\n    * [Vendor Model](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#vendor-model)\n    * [Direct User Access Model](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/#direct-user-access-model)\n\n\nCopyright \u00a9 2026 Rigetti Computing.\n",
